Druzzil Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf Elemental</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/29/01 5:11:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Request hunting guide -- Crystalline Shardwurms in GD</span><hr size=1> Ok, I believe these wurms are in a large cave under the mountain.<br>
<br>
To get there, head down the river from Thurgadin.  Head all the way through the caves, and take the last left before exiting the caves.  Follow the tunnel, and take the second right.  This should put you in a short tunnel that dead-ends into the crystalline wurm cave.  If not, it's around there somewhere ;)<br>
<br>
There are 4 crystalline wurms in the corners of the cave, and one wanderer that visits the small tunnel.  Keep harmony handy if you have to move or fight near a static spawn, and steer clear of the wanderer.  Root/Dot with help works well.  The first couple fights are tricky, but once you've cleared one or two spawn spots, you have room to move around.<br>
<br>
With a couple caster/bard friends, this camp is a nice change of pace.  The xp is bad, the spell drops can be frustrating, but killing big wurms has always been fun  :)  Fighting in a big cave is cool too.<br>
<br>
If you must fight outside, it is possible to aggro a crys wurm, and harmony / snare anything else that jumps you as you coax it outside.  Druids make great pullers from this cave, but I preferred fighting inside since the wurms tend to warp back to their spawn spots.<br>
<br>
good luck,<br>
<br>
-Quelm, 58 Preserver<br>
Drunken Tsunami, Terris-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umalikaiiscariot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malikai Iscariot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cs.fsu.edu/~padgett/swirl.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/30/01 8:37:59 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cs.fsu.edu/~padgett/Malikai.jpg height=193 width=154></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Request hunting guide -- Crystalline Shardwurms in GD</span><hr size=1> Enter the caves from the southern entrance and take the first right, then take the 2nd right for the huge room with the crystallines.  Upon entering the huge room, you will notice a crystalline wurm to your immediate left and to your right.  If soloing, I would center myself in the cave (don't get too close to the 3 spawn directly in front of you) and root, stack dots, and ensnare one of the wurms either on the right or left of you.  It's a bit tricky and they have a ton of hit points, when root breaks, you don't have too much room to manuever - but there is enough to run the wurm around close to his spawn point and re-root.  Once one is dead, med up and tackle the spawn across from it.  Spawntime is fairly quick and when I was soloing, would only be able to keep one spawn dead at a time.  I did it a bit pre-54 dot and it was quite challenging - vambraces were a necessity. <p><p><table><tr><td style="filter:glow(color=darkblue strength=3);font-family:arial;font-weight: BOLD;font-size:'10pt'">
